cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI 

This paper focuses on improving the experience of workers in completing tasks on crowdsourcing platforms by explicitly eliciting their preferences. This topic is closely related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it aims to improve the interaction between workers and the platform. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to build worker models, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper proposes a generic framework for preference elicitation, which could be relevant to the field of cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
